SIMPLE: wearing
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wearing
<hw>Wear"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of one who wears; the manner in which a thing wears; use; conduct;
consumption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Belike he meant to ward, and there to see his
<qex>wearing</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is worn; clothes; garments.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give me my nightly <qex>wearing</qex> and adieu.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wearing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wearing
<hw>Wear"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
designed for, wear; <as>as, <ex>wearing</ex> apparel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wearish</ent>⟦br⟧
